whole lot of "something."

212
00:12:24,047 --> 00:12:26,047
Oh, this is where you
tell us to back off,

213
00:12:26,048 --> 00:12:27,582
let you do your job?

214
00:12:27,583 --> 00:12:29,016
No, no, no. This is where
I say, "I get it."

215
00:12:29,017 --> 00:12:30,584
When you lose someone
that you love,

216
00:12:30,585 --> 00:12:31,854
the hardest thing
is to do nothing.

217
00:12:31,855 --> 00:12:34,689
May I?

218
00:12:35,925 --> 00:12:38,026
Police have any new leads?

219
00:12:38,027 --> 00:12:39,728
Not as many as we do.

220
00:12:39,729 --> 00:12:41,062
I don't understand.

221
00:12:41,063 --> 00:12:43,466
We don't know much about
your wife, Mr. Galliston,

222
00:12:43,467 --> 00:12:45,967
but we know quite a bit
about who might have her.

223
00:12:45,968 --> 00:12:48,203
You see, we've been
working on this case

224
00:12:48,204 --> 00:12:50,171
for a very, very long time.

225
00:12:53,042 --> 00:12:54,876
This was taken

226
00:12:54,877 --> 00:12:57,146
